{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_018G5NWJFoNBQ5vJiLUvvtMW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete and verified.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe demo app is now exposed at `http://demo.example.com/app` — the test request returns exit code 0 and prints `hello`.\n\n**What I created** (in `/tmp/expose.yaml`, applied to the cluster):\n\n1. **Service `demo-app`** — selects pods with `app=demo-app`, exposes port `80` → targetPort `5678` (the container's port).\n\n2. **Ingress `demo-app`** — uses `ingressClassName: nginx`, routes host `demo.example.com` path `/app` (Prefix) to the Service on port 80.\n\n**Key detail:** the app only serves the root path `/`, so a request to `/app` would 404 at the backend. I added the `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /` annotation so nginx rewrites the incoming `/app` to `/` before proxying. The Deployment was not touched.\n\nVerification: endpoints are populated (`10.244.0.149:5678`), HTTP status `200`, body `hello`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":459,"cache_read_input_tokens":30639,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":459},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e7b6fe4c-86ae-45c0-8628-80698543430e","uuid":"1545bffe-f53b-41cd-97eb-f7875d07e974","request_id":"req_011CcAaK9ChjDs25RD2aANqG"}
